HEADWORD: homburg
<hw>hom"burg</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from <etsep>Homburg</etsep>,
Germany, the place of first manufacture.]</ety> <def>A felt hat with a
crown that is creased lengthwise, and a brim that is slightly curled
upward at the edge.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fedora, felt hat, trilby.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

